KW  - Bank acquisition
KW  - Share price reaction
KW  - Valuation effects
KW  - Pre-acquisition bank performance
AB  - This study measures the abnormal performance of banks subsequent to their acquisitions of other banks. We find a strong negative share price reaction following the acquisition, which tends to continue over a 36-month period. The results suggest that banks generally do not realize the potential benefits from acquisitions, or that any advantages are offset. The long-run valuation effects across the acquiring banks were found to be more favorable for banks that (1) made acquisitions within their existing markets, (2) experienced relatively poor pre-acquisition performance, and (3) had relatively low pre-acquisition growth.
